<p>Standard HTML heading elements (<code>{{ '<h1>' | escape }}</code> â€“ <code>{{ '<h6>' | escape }}</code>) have no styles applied to them by default. To give these elements the style of a heading, you have three options:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Apply the <code>.heading</code> class, which sets <code>font-family</code>, <code>line-height</code>, and <code>font-weight</code>, as well as a font size utility</li>
  <li>Apply one of the <code>.heading-{1-6}</code> classes, which in addition to the properties set by <code>.heading</code> sets <code>font-size</code></li>
  <li>Use a set of utility classes, like <code>.text-xl</code>, <code>.text-heading</code>, and <code>.lh-heading</code> to achieve a custom heading look</li>
</ul>

<p>Sometimes you want to match the font styling of a heading but cannot use an associated HTML element, therefore classes are favored over simply styling the HTML elements itself.</p>

