<h2>Combining headings</h2>

<p>You can combine heading elements. The <code>.subheading</code> class provides the same functionality as its main counterpart, except setting the <code>font-weight</code> to <code>light</code>.</p>

<p>As a rule of thumb, it is recommended to use a size difference of two. So if you use a <code>.heading-1</code>, combine it with a <code>.subheading-3</code>.

<style>
/* Counteract `.content` styles to achieve normal behaviour */
.heading-1 + .subheading-3,
.heading-2 + .subheading-4,
.heading-3 + .subheading-5 {
  margin-top: calc(-1 * var(--space-m));
}
</style>

{% snippet %}
<p class="heading-1">Heading 1</p>
<p class="subheading-3 text-gray-dark">Subheading 3</p>

<p class="heading-2">Heading 2</p>
<p class="subheading-4">Subheading 4</p>

<p class="heading-3">Heading 3</p>
<p class="subheading-5">Subheading 5</p>
{% endsnippet %}
